This paper discusses the impact of biased training data on machine learning algorithms, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the role of decision-making and selection bias, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also touches on issues related to fairness and discrimination, which are relevant to the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
